⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Comet
node N1 · N1 · ⟦The Comet:N1:42a62f⟧

WHO   — The Comet — the seer's celestial omen
WHAT  — The archetype of the omen overhead — the bearded star that the seer reads as the harbinger of a king's death, of war, of plague and overturning; the sky as a page on which fate is inscribed in light.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Michel de Nostredame inherited a cosmos in which the heavens were a script and the astrologer a reader; because a comet, breaking the fixed order of the spheres, could only mean the breaking of the order below; because to see the sign was to read the sentence.
HOW   — By judicial astrology and the lore of portents — eclipses, conjunctions, the sudden bearded star — woven through the quatrains in allusive verse so that the omen above always answers to the upheaval below.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  When the bearded star burns, the order below is already breaking — I only read aloud what the sky had written.

spoken token : thyx-stuk-kreim   ·   hex : 42a62f
